    <section id="page-model1" class="hidden">
      <div class="hero">
        <h1>Model 1 Enterprise platform PM case study</h1>
        <p>Best for platform, SaaS, workflow, and internal product roles.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Overview</h2>
          <p><strong>Product:</strong> [Subscription billing and order management platform]</p>
          <p><strong>Users:</strong> [Sales ops, finance ops, customer success, provisioning teams]</p>
          <p><strong>Problem:</strong> [Manual steps and inconsistent data caused billing errors and delayed fulfillment]</p>
          <p><strong>My role:</strong> [Owned requirements, prioritization, and delivery coordination across product, engineering, and finance stakeholders]</p>

          <h3>Context and constraints</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Multiple upstream systems: CRM, CPQ, ERP, provisioning</li>
            <li>Regulatory and audit needs for invoicing and revenue</li>
            <li>Global regions with different tax and payment flows</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>What I did</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Defined end to end workflow from quote to invoice with clear system of record boundaries</li>
            <li>Authored epics, user stories, and acceptance criteria tied to financial controls</li>
            <li>Designed a release plan with phased rollout and rollback criteria</li>
            <li>Led UAT strategy with reconciliation test cases against source systems</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Tradeoffs and decisions</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Decision: [Defer low volume edge cases to phase two to protect timeline]</li>
            <li>Decision: [Standardize data mapping even if it created short term change management]</li>
            <li>Decision: [Prioritize billing accuracy over new features in the first release]</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Outcomes</h3>
          <div class="kpis">
            <div class="kpi"><div class="label">Billing defect reduction</div><div class="value">[X percent]</div></div>
            <div class="kpi"><div class="label">Cycle time improvement</div><div class="value">[X days faster]</div></div>
            <div class="kpi"><div class="label">Automation added</div><div class="value">[X workflows]</div></div>
            <div class="kpi"><div class="label">Annualized impact</div><div class="value">[Dollar value or range]</div></div>
          </div>

          <h3>What I would do next</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Add observability metrics for order failures and invoice exceptions</li>
            <li>Introduce self serve admin tooling for billing adjustments with approvals</li>
            <li>Move from manual reconciliations to automated anomaly detection</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h2>Artifacts you can attach</h2>
          <p>Use your own sanitized diagrams.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Workflow diagram showing system boundaries and handoffs</li>
            <li>Backlog snapshot with prioritization rationale</li>
            <li>UAT plan and reconciliation matrix</li>
            <li>Release readiness checklist and risk log</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Interview angles</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>How you handled conflicting stakeholder priorities</li>
            <li>How you defined success metrics and monitored them</li>
            <li>How you managed risk in finance impacting releases</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="footer">
            Replace all bracketed fields. Keep it to what you can defend in an interview.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
