    <section id="page-model2" class="hidden">
      <div class="hero">
        <h1>Model 2 Revenue finance and deal desk case study</h1>
        <p>Best for FP&A, revenue finance, deal desk, and commercial finance adjacent roles.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Overview</h2>
          <p><strong>Business goal:</strong> [Improve revenue predictability and reduce invoice exceptions]</p>
          <p><strong>Scope:</strong> [Bookings to billings to revenue alignment for subscription contracts]</p>
          <p><strong>Stakeholders:</strong> [Finance, sales ops, legal, billing ops, customer success]</p>
          <p><strong>My role:</strong> [Built operating model, controls, and reporting with data backed recommendations]</p>

          <h3>Problem framing</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Invoice exceptions created delayed cash collection and customer escalations</li>
            <li>Contract terms were not consistently structured for billing and revenue rules</li>
            <li>Forecast accuracy suffered due to inconsistent operational data</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Analysis performed</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Built a driver tree linking contract attributes to billing outcomes</li>
            <li>Segmented exception causes by region, product, and contract type</li>
            <li>Quantified impact on cash timing and revenue timing</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Solution and controls</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Standardized contract data requirements and validation rules</li>
            <li>Introduced approval workflow for non standard terms</li>
            <li>Created weekly exception review operating cadence with owners</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Outcomes</h3>
          <div class="kpis">
            <div class="kpi"><div class="label">Exception rate</div><div class="value">[X percent down]</div></div>
            <div class="kpi"><div class="label">Cash collection timing</div><div class="value">[X days faster]</div></div>
            <div class="kpi"><div class="label">Forecast accuracy</div><div class="value">[X percent improvement]</div></div>
            <div class="kpi"><div class="label">Manual effort reduced</div><div class="value">[X hours per week]</div></div>
          </div>

          <h3>What I learned</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Finance outcomes improve most when you fix upstream data capture</li>
            <li>Controls must be paired with a repeatable operating cadence</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h2>Artifacts you can attach</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Driver tree for exceptions and root causes</li>
            <li>Sample finance ready definition of done for billing changes</li>
            <li>Dashboard mock showing bookings, billings, revenue and exceptions</li>
            <li>Control checklist aligned to revenue impacting fields</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Interview angles</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>How you quantified financial impact without perfect data</li>
            <li>How you managed stakeholder disagreements about controls</li>
            <li>How you prevented recurrence, not just fixed one off issues</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="footer">
            This model is strong for finance transitions because it speaks in outcomes finance teams own.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

