      <div class="hero">
        <h1>Model 3 Product adoption and analytics case study</h1>
        <p>Best for customer success platforms, product ops, analytics driven PM roles.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Overview</h2>
          <p><strong>Product area:</strong> [Customer onboarding and adoption]</p>
          <p><strong>Goal:</strong> [Increase activation and reduce time to value]</p>
          <p><strong>My role:</strong> [Defined metrics, instrumented flows, and ran experiments with cross functional teams]</p>

          <h3>Baseline and metrics</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Activation definition: <code class="inline">[first invoice created OR first successful transaction]</code></li>
            <li>Time to value: <code class="inline">[days from contract to first successful usage]</code></li>
            <li>Adoption funnel: <code class="inline">[Invite → Setup → First use → Repeat use]</code></li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Insights</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Primary drop off at [step] due to missing prerequisites and unclear guidance</li>
            <li>Secondary drop off driven by [role based permissions or data quality]</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>What I shipped</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Improved onboarding flow with contextual prompts and clear error states</li>
            <li>Created lifecycle emails and in app guidance tied to user behavior</li>
            <li>Partnered with CS to build playbooks for high risk accounts</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Experiment design</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Hypothesis: [Changing step order reduces setup time]</li>
            <li>Success metric: [activation rate]</li>
            <li>Guardrails: [support tickets, churn signals]</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Outcomes</h3>
          <div class="kpis">
            <div class="kpi"><div class="label">Activation rate</div><div class="value">[X percent up]</div></div>
            <div class="kpi"><div class="label">Time to value</div><div class="value">[X days down]</div></div>
            <div class="kpi"><div class="label">Support tickets</div><div class="value">[X percent down]</div></div>
            <div class="kpi"><div class="label">Adoption cohort</div><div class="value">[X percent retention lift]</div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h2>Artifacts you can attach</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Funnel chart and cohort chart mockups</li>
            <li>Event taxonomy table for instrumentation</li>
            <li>Experiment readout one pager</li>
            <li>Onboarding playbook outline</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Interview angles</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>How you defined activation and defended it</li>
            <li>How you balanced experiments with enterprise constraints</li>
            <li>How you partnered with CS and engineering for adoption</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="footer">
            This model is strong if the job emphasizes metrics, onboarding, and adoption.
